<TITLE> Former BNP lawmaker Dewan Salahuddin faces extortion case </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Savar, July 2 (bdnews24.com) -- An extortion case has been filed against former BNP lawmaker Dewan Mohammad Salauddin and three others with Savar cognizance court on charges of extortion, police said Monday. Savar Upazila Awami League executive committee member and Upazila Hawkers' League chairman Abdul Quader Mollah filed the case against the ex-MP from Dhaka-12 constituency. The three other accused are Municipal Hawkers' Dal general secretary Aminul Islam, vice chairman Md Shahabuddin and organising secretary Mahabub Ullah Babu. The case statement alleges that the gang of three attacked the plaintiff's business at Shahjalal Market and looted Tk 30,000 in cash, directed by Salauddin, in October 2006. The raiders also tried to extort another Tk 1 lakh, according to case details. The cognizance court magistrate ordered an investigation into the case. Sub-inspector Nasim Uddin of Savar Police Station said the police would open an investigation as soon as the court order reaches them. Two cases have so far been filed against Salauddin. The first case was filed with Savar Police Station on June 24. bdnews24.c
